###########################
#  Initialization

DOCUMENT();

loadMacros(
"PGstandard.pl",
"MathObjects.pl",
"AnswerFormatHelp.pl",
"PGML.pl",
"PGcourse.pl",
);

TEXT(beginproblem());
$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 1;

###########################
#  Setup

Context()->variables->add(t=>"Real");
Context()->flags->set(
  tolerance => 0.051,
  tolType => "absolute",
);

$m = random(2, 10, 2);
$A = random(100, 200, 10);

$a = 2;
$b = $m;
$c = -2*$A;
$a2 = -$c;

$height = Compute("(-$b + sqrt($b**2 - 4*$a*$c))/(2*$a)");
$base = Compute("2*$height + $m");


###########################
#  Main text

BEGIN_PGML
The area of a triangular flower bed in the park is [`[$A]`] square feet.  The base is [`[$m]`] feet longer than twice the height.  Find the base and height.  Round to the nearest tenth.

Height = [_______________]{$height}feet

Base =  [_______________]{$base}feet

[@ AnswerFormatHelp("numbers") @]*

END_PGML


############################
#  Solution

BEGIN_PGML_SOLUTION
[`b = 2x + [$m]`]

[`h = x`]

The area of a triangle is [`A = \frac{1}{2}bh`]

[`\frac{1}{2}x(2x + [$m])=[$A]`]

Multiply both sides by 2:

[`x(2x + [$m]) = [$a2]`]

[`2x^2 + [$m]x = [$a2]`]

[`2x^2 + [$m]x - [$a2] = 0`]

Solve for x using the quadratic formula:

[`` x = \frac{-b \pm \sqrt{b^2 - 4ac}}{2a}``]

[`` x = \frac{-[$m] \pm \sqrt{[$m]^2 - 4\cdot 2 \cdot [$c]}}{2\cdot 2}``]

Only the positive solution makes sense, so [`x = [$height]`].

The base is [`b = 2\cdot [$height] + [$m] = [$base]`]

END_PGML_SOLUTION

COMMENT('MathObject version. Uses PGML.');

ENDDOCUMENT();